{
  "slug": "avatar-fire-and-ash-burns-bright-before-flaming-out-plus-bes",
  "title": "‘Avatar: Fire and Ash’ Burns Bright Before Flaming Out. Plus: Best Picture Power Rankings and the Oscar Short Lists!",
  "show": "The Big Picture",
  "network": "The Ringer",
  "hosts": [
    "Sean Fennessey",
    "Amanda Dobbins"
  ],
  "published": "2025-12-19",
  "runtimeMin": 82,
  "format": "James Cameron's third Pandora trip splits the room. The Oscar short lists land in 12 categories, and the Best Picture rankings get their last reshuffle of 2025.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "kind": "discussion",
      "heading": "The Oscars Leave ABC for YouTube, Plus the ‘Disclosure’ Trailer",
      "note": "the news up top",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Disclosure Day",
          "year": 2026,
          "note": "The Spielberg alien thriller with Emily Blunt and Josh O'Connor, out June. The hosts weren't sure of the title on air and guessed 'Disclosure.' Sean flagged some CGI shots (a girl, a moose, a bird) as Zemeckis-'Here'-adjacent, but loved the practical car chase."
        },
        {
          "title": "Close Encounters of the Third Kind",
          "year": 1977,
          "note": "Cited as part of the Spielberg alien lineage."
        },
        {
          "title": "E.T. the Extra-Terrestrial",
          "year": 1982,
          "note": "Same lineage."
        },
        {
          "title": "War of the Worlds",
          "year": 2005,
          "note": "The Spielberg predecessor the new trailer echoes."
        },
        {
          "title": "Gladiator II",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "Evidence for the 'old directors still going big' trend (Ridley Scott)."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Last Duel",
          "year": 2021,
          "note": "The other late Ridley Scott swing."
        },
        {
          "title": "Killers of the Flower Moon",
          "year": 2023,
          "note": "Scorsese, same trend."
        },
        {
          "title": "Megalopolis",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "Coppola, same trend."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "review",
      "heading": "‘Avatar: Fire and Ash’",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Avatar: Fire and Ash",
          "year": 2025,
          "note": "The split verdict: Amanda's out ('the experiment has run out'), Sean liked it on strength of its highs. Both grant the craft is a different league, both fault it for replaying the first films beat-for-beat and for pacing that drags once the family is scattered. Highs: the jellyfish-dragon battle, Quaritch's psychedelic seduction by Varang, the third-act squids. Oona Chaplin's Varang is the standout. Sean predicts $1.6B and doubts a fourth and fifth film."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "discussion",
      "heading": "The Oscar Short Lists",
      "note": "12 categories announced",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Sirât",
          "year": 2025,
          "note": "The shocker: shortlisted 5 times, including casting. Oliver Laxe's Spanish film (a rave in the desert) that nobody pegged as an Academy movie. Landed at No. 10 in the power rankings."
        },
        {
          "title": "Weapons",
          "year": 2025,
          "note": "Surprise casting nod; with Amy Madigan looking like a lock, it jumps to tier 1."
        },
        {
          "title": "Sinners",
          "year": 2025,
          "note": "Shortlisted 8 times; an 'interesting Sinners moment' with real spoiler potential."
        },
        {
          "title": "Wicked for Good",
          "year": 2025,
          "note": "Also shortlisted 8 times."
        },
        {
          "title": "Frankenstein",
          "year": 2025,
          "note": "Six shortlistings, which isn't a surprise."
        },
        {
          "title": "Marty Supreme",
          "year": 2025,
          "note": "Only missed in sound, which the hosts would have liked to see."
        },
        {
          "title": "Jay Kelly",
          "year": 2025,
          "note": "Absent from casting and cinematography, which looks like a DOA sign and makes them nervous about Adam Sandler."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Testament of Ann Lee",
          "year": 2025,
          "note": "Shut out entirely; Searchlight looks likely to miss Best Picture for the first time since 2016."
        },
        {
          "title": "No Other Choice",
          "year": 2025,
          "note": "Gorgeously shot but snubbed in cinematography; it turns up across the lists without dominating any of them."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Secret Agent",
          "year": 2025,
          "note": "Casting nod is a good sign for the Brazilian film."
        },
        {
          "title": "Hamnet",
          "year": 2025,
          "note": "In score despite reused Max Richter music, which didn't disqualify it."
        },
        {
          "title": "A House of Dynamite",
          "year": 2025,
          "note": "A score look for a movie otherwise thin across the lists."
        },
        {
          "title": "Hedda",
          "year": 2025,
          "note": "Another score nod, for a film that's barely shown up elsewhere on the lists."
        },
        {
          "title": "Wake Up Dead Man: A Knives Out Mystery",
          "year": 2025,
          "note": "In score only, not a great sign for the film more broadly."
        },
        {
          "title": "Captain America: Brave New World",
          "year": 2025,
          "note": "In score; Laura Karpman (of the jazzy 'American Fiction') composed it."
        }
      ]
    },
